h3. Summary
When updating a page with REST API, if the "title" of the page is not defined, Confluence returns a 500 error message with NullPointerException

h3. Environment
* Confluence REST API

h3. Steps to Reproduce
Following [Confluence REST API Examples|https://developer.atlassian.com/display/CONFDEV/Confluence+REST+API+Examples#ConfluenceRESTAPIExamples-Manipulatingcontent]
# Run the following call to create a page: (change credentials and URL)
# {noformat}
curl -u user:password -X POST -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d'{"type":"page","title":"test page","space":{"key":"ds"},"body":{"storage":{"value":"<p>This is a new page</p>","representation":"storage"}}}' https://<my-confluence-url>/rest/api/content/
{noformat}
# Get the page ID from the result and use it in the following command to Update the page:
{noformat}
curl -u user:password -X PUT -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"type":"page","version":{"number":2},"title":"test page","body":{"storage":{"value":"<p>This is the updated text for the test page</p>","representation":"storage"}}}' https://<my-confluence-url>/wiki/rest/api/content/<page-id>
{noformat}
# Ty to update again but without the *"title"* 
{noformat}
curl -u user:password -X PUT -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"type":"page","version":{"number":3},"body":{"storage":{"value":"<p>This is the updated text for the test page 3</p>","representation":"storage"}}}' https://<my-confluence-url>/wiki/rest/api/content/<page-id>
{noformat}
Note: there is also a required increment in version in the query.

h3. Expected Results
A 400 error is received with a descriptive message pointing out that the "title" is required.

h3. Actual Results
500 error is received
{noformat}
{"statusCode":500,"message":"java.lang.NullPointerException: null"}
{noformat}
 
h3. Notes
Confluence Logs:
{noformat}
