h3. Summary
Confluence REST API is returning a 500 error on some specific queries that used to work on previous Confluence releases.

Error is: 
{noformat}
"statusCode":500,"message":"net.sf.hibernate.LazyInitializationException: Failed to lazily initialize a collection - no session or session was closed"
{noformat}

h3. Environment
* Confluence 6.0

h3. Steps to reproduce:
This requires a page with title 'Test' in the Demonstration Space
# Run a search on a space with expanded content: (/) Works
{noformat}
curl -u user:password -X GET "https://instance.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/search?cql=space=DS&expand=space,children.page,ancestors,version"
{noformat}
# Run a similar search but increasing the limit: (x) Fails
{noformat}
curl -u user:password -X GET "https://instance.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/search?cql=space=DS&expand=space,children.page,ancestors,version&limit=100"
{"statusCode":500,"message":"net.sf.hibernate.LazyInitializationException: Failed to lazily initialize a collection - no session or session was closed"}
{noformat}
# Run a similar search as 1 but adding CQL "AND type=page": (x) Fails
{noformat}
curl -u user:password -X GET "https://instance.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/search?cql=space=DS%20AND%20type=page&expand=space,children.page,ancestors,version"
{"statusCode":500,"message":"net.sf.hibernate.LazyInitializationException: Failed to lazily initialize a collection - no session or session was closed"}
{noformat}
# Run a similar search as 3 but removing the children '.pages':  (/) Works
{noformat}
curl -u user:password -X GET "https://instance.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/search?cql=space=DS%20AND%20type=page&expand=space,children,ancestors,version"
{noformat}

*Expected Results:*
All 4 queries return results and work as on previous Confluence versions.
 
h3. Notes
Tested working on Confluence 5.9.4 Server

h3. Summary
When you want user with access only to Confluence be able to see issues from a public project using the macro JIRA issue/filter inside a Confluence page, the error "JIRA server returned a trusted apps erro: PERMISSION_DENIED; Permission Denied; []" shows up.
!Screen.png|thumbnail!
Any other macro from the same project will be displayed properly on the same page.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Set the project on JIRA set as public;
# Go to a page on Confluence > Edit > Select the macro 'JIRA issue/filter';
# Set the public project;
# Save;
# Open the page using a user with access only to Confluence.

*Expected behaviour*
* The macro should display the issues from the project.

*Actual behaviour*
* When the user opens the page the macro is not working and showing the error:
{noformat}
IRA server returned a trusted apps erro: PERMISSION_DENIED; Permission Denied; []
{noformat}

Version: Confluence 5.9.1-OD-62-023 and 5.9.1-OD-65-062

h3.Workaround
No workaround so far.

