It's possible for Confluence to start and not be able to access a DocumentBuilderFactory from within core, or most plugins. This is most likely to happen when a plugin is the first class to initialize the JAXP ServiceLoader, and because Confluence and the other plugins are in different classloaders to the bound plugin, none of those other components can render content any more.

